Dialogue: Sorry, got a kind of an important meeting.
Nothing to worry about! Just – work. So yeah, couldn’t sleep.
Sometimes I thought I was asleep and I actually wasn’t. It was weird.
But you looked like—
Well my nasal strip fell off. What’s this?
Ooooh! Okay!
Yeah. It means it’s really happening? We’re getting married!
You know what, I’m not even going to look at this. Just show me
where to sign.
Honestly, honey, I’m not from money, you’re from money. I don’t
want to look at it. I hereby comply.
Fine. Look, as a gesture of my love to you, I will have my lawyer look
at it. But I want you to know, in my head I already signed it.

the students taped back together the shredded documents from the US

No, sure. Absolutely.
Oh no sure. Totally. I get it.
Hey, buddy. What’s up? Am I going to see you in the office any time
soon?
Uh-huh. So what’s your
Excuse me? Canada? Canada with the healthcare and the ennui?
Why’s that, cock-sock?
Greg, fuck your grandpa.

Well, hurry up, Greg, yeah? I have a job for you. And I’m being nice
cos I’m on speakerphone but if I wasn’t on speakerphone I’d be being,
shall we say, somewhat less agreeable? Yeah?

Christmas—
or New Year.

No. No. It’s fine.
Nothing, it’s just my lawyer says—

I mean, that’s a legal term. I don’t care—

I know, but your dad loves it!
I mean, do we even need to have one?
But we’re not going to divorce.
I am expecting to die, Shiv. Sorry, maybe I should have mentioned
that when we first started dating.
Happy Thanksgiving!
There you are!
How was the trip? I hear Grandpa Ewan’s quite the character?
Uh-huh uh-huh. So listen. I actually need you to go into the office
today. That cool?
Has to be today.
Exactly. Greg. Listen to me.
What do you want to do?
With your life? Where do you want to be in five years’ time? What
are your hopes?
What are your fears?
You and I have had our bumps, Greg. But I want you to trust me. And
I want to be able to trust you. Yes?
I have absolutely no idea.
It has nothing to do with me. And we never had this conversation.
You just need to go to the office. Sign out some boxes, do some
shredding and meet some lovely guys?
Why are you making this a big deal, Greg? It’s not a big deal. A
chimp could do this, Greg! A little chimpanzee!
Oh, did they bring cranberry sauce too?
I think – Marcia’s son?
Okay, soldier. You ready? Just getting the deets!
Hey man!
Good handshake. Firm. I can already tell I’m going to like you.
And I’ve shaken a lot of hands. A lot. Handshake buddies! Okay you!
Okay. These are the file numbers. This is the room number. You
good?
Why are you calling me? Do not call me. Is there a problem? Don’t
tell me if there’s a problem. Don’t tell me anything. Your phone
shouldn’t even be on.
Well you know what to do?
It’s okay. Greg! Of course it’s okay. It’s a job.
I thought Canadians only fought on ice!
Do you think it’s all going to be okay?
So apparently your lawyer is talking to my lawyer.
Yeah. She’s got all excited about bumps and tiered share option tie-ins
for my sperm count et cetera and I’m just saying no no, but she
noticed re infidelities there’s no—
Cos that’s not going to happen.
Yes.
Meaning?
I don’t travel that much?
Does shit happen?
Thank you.
All good?
I don’t want to know and don’t ever tell me. But well done. Here.
Welcome to the family.
Hey listen, I have an idea. We should do what my family do at
Thanksgiving …?
We go around and say what we’re thankful for?
I can’t go first. I need to go last because … I’d like to go last.
I think we’re all thankful for that. That goes without saying.
And I’m thankful that I’m going to be marrying into one of the most –
interesting and vital and—
kind and loving families in the world!
Congratulations on your ‘next steps’.
I’m interested to know what ‘next steps’ actually means. Is there a
greeting card I can buy that says, ‘Congratulations on next steps’?
Is there a ceremony? Or is it more of a financial arrangement?
Hey hey hey! Captain Spooner coming in to spoon!
What?
Yeah. Smart. I was never sure about her.
It’s not a biggie. I don’t like any pols, Shiv.
You can have some of my air!
Oh fuck, my eye.
